verses.verse: To the chief Musician<WH5329> upon Neginah<WH5058>, A Psalm of David<WH1732>. Hear<WH8085> my cry<WH7440>, O God<WH430>; attend<WH7181> unto my prayer<WH8605>.
From the end<WH7097> of the earth<WH776> will I cry<WH7121> unto thee, when my heart<WH3820> is overwhelmed<WH5848>: lead<WH5148> me to the rock<WH6697> that is higher<WH7311> than I.
For thou hast been a shelter<WH4268> for me, and a strong<WH5797> tower<WH4026> from<WH6440> the enemy<WH341>.
I will abide<WH1481> in thy tabernacle<WH168> for ever<WH5769>: I will trust<WH2620> in the covert<WH5643> of thy wings<WH3671>. Selah<WH5542>.
For thou, O God<WH430>, hast heard<WH8085> my vows<WH5088>: thou hast given<WH5414> me the heritage<WH3425> of those that fear<WH3373> thy name<WH8034>.
Thou wilt prolong<WH3254> the king's<WH4428> life<WH3117><WH3117>: and his years<WH8141> as many<WH1755> generations<WH1755>.
He shall abide<WH3427> before<WH6440> God<WH430> for ever<WH5769>: O prepare<WH4487> mercy<WH2617> and truth<WH571>, which may preserve<WH5341> him.
So will I sing<WH2167> praise unto thy name<WH8034> for ever<WH5703>, that I may daily<WH3117><WH3117> perform<WH7999> my vows<WH5088>.
